text:
Broadway, west side, at West 167th Street, showing units of. Columbia-Presbyterian Medical Center, extending from 165th to 168th Streets, as seen across St. Nicholas Ave. (foreground) and Mitchell Square. The 11-story building on the left is the Babies Hospital; directly west of it and across the foot-bridge is the Presbyterian (Sloane) Hospital; on its right, the 2-story Admitting unit and adjoining that is the Vanderbilt Clinic of the College of Physicians and Surgeons (Columbia University).

1936.

W.P.A. Photo.
Federal Writers Project.
